1
00:00:55,145 --> 00:00:55,879
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:55,879 --> 00:00:56,713
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:56,713 --> 00:00:57,514
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:57,514 --> 00:00:58,282
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:01:05,222 --> 00:01:07,591
(Mono Group Chairman Choi Young Ho
shares warmth for the Korean New Year.)

6
00:01:07,591 --> 00:01:09,393
(Joins Hope 2025 Sharing Campaign
for sustainable CSR)

7
00:01:09,393 --> 00:01:11,828
(Visited a flophouse district
to volunteer and offer support)

8
00:01:14,331 --> 00:01:15,365
(Mono Group's major overseas projects
moving smoothly)

9
00:01:15,365 --> 00:01:16,300
(Record-breaking performance
expected this year)

10
00:01:17,267 --> 00:01:18,502
(Successful overseas expansion continues)

11
00:01:20,470 --> 00:01:21,738
(The hidden architect behind the veil)

12
00:01:21,738 --> 00:01:22,973
(Chairman Choi Young Ho's
suspicious master plan)

13
00:01:22,973 --> 00:01:24,107
(The illusion of delegated management,
Mono Group's dual structure)

14
00:01:27,244 --> 00:01:28,779
(The hidden architect behind the veil)

15
00:01:28,779 --> 00:01:30,347
(Chairman Choi Young Ho's
suspicious master plan)

16
00:01:31,949 --> 00:01:34,851
Choi Young Ho made a fortune
in overseas construction.

17
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:38,021
Starting with nothing,
he's come this far...

18
00:01:38,422 --> 00:01:40,490
with almost no real enemies,

19
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:43,260
which proves his business sense
and ability are exceptional.

20
00:01:50,867 --> 00:01:52,669
(Mono Group)

21
00:01:53,437 --> 00:01:55,138
It's the company he founded,

22
00:01:55,572 --> 00:01:58,542
but for the past few years, he's entrusted
management to Vice Chairman Yoo Min Ho,

23
00:01:59,309 --> 00:02:01,945
and is known to retain
only final decision-making authority.

24
00:02:03,213 --> 00:02:04,481
But many still believe...

25
00:02:04,481 --> 00:02:06,883
he continues to direct and decide
everything behind the scenes,

26
00:02:07,884 --> 00:02:09,720
so he's definitely a man
who is not what he appears to be.

27
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:12,322
(Choi Hee Su's fiancé - Ryu Jun Ho)

28
00:02:18,195 --> 00:02:20,931
It feels like he's deliberately keeping
his domestic activities to a minimum...

29
00:02:21,632 --> 00:02:23,166
in several different ways.

30
00:02:24,601 --> 00:02:26,403
He's so shrouded in secrecy...

31
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:28,705
and spends most of his time overseas...

32
00:02:29,306 --> 00:02:31,008
that getting close to him is impossible.

33
00:02:34,578 --> 00:02:37,681
I've heard people say
his plane is his office.

34
00:02:41,218 --> 00:02:43,587
(Kim Soo Yeon)

35
00:02:43,854 --> 00:02:44,855
Mom.

36
00:02:46,223 --> 00:02:48,392
Mom, I'm here.

37
00:02:48,392 --> 00:02:50,327
His wife passed away a few years ago.

38
00:02:51,161 --> 00:02:52,496
Since then,

39
00:02:52,496 --> 00:02:54,865
he's been spending far more time overseas.

40
00:02:55,866 --> 00:02:57,701
He has a daughter studying abroad,

41
00:02:58,669 --> 00:03:00,804
and she's probably around your age.

42
00:03:01,338 --> 00:03:04,041
Whatever it is,
if it comes out of that girl's mouth,

43
00:03:04,041 --> 00:03:05,776
you can assume anything is possible.

44
00:03:06,677 --> 00:03:08,345
She's his only blood relative,

45
00:03:08,345 --> 00:03:09,980
so apparently, he's very attached to her.

46
00:03:17,521 --> 00:03:18,488
This house?

47
00:03:19,856 --> 00:03:21,024
It was listed at five million dollars...

48
00:03:21,024 --> 00:03:22,225
Just like you said,

49
00:03:22,225 --> 00:03:23,894
that girl, Choi Hee Su,

50
00:03:24,361 --> 00:03:25,829
got a place in Hanyeon-dong.

51
00:03:26,797 --> 00:03:29,032
You'll need to find out
exactly where it is.

52
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,168
Of course.

53
00:03:32,302 --> 00:03:33,303
She's lived abroad for a long time,

54
00:03:33,303 --> 00:03:35,072
so she likely doesn't know
many people in Korea.

55
00:03:36,306 --> 00:03:38,308
That means she'll spend
a lot of time at home.

56
00:03:43,146 --> 00:03:45,182
Choi Hee Su bought a building
worth over five million dollars...

57
00:03:45,182 --> 00:03:46,550
and uses it as a studio,

58
00:03:47,484 --> 00:03:50,020
but the neighbors say
they've barely even seen her face.

59
00:03:51,588 --> 00:03:52,956
She has a closed-off personality,

60
00:03:53,523 --> 00:03:55,225
so getting close to her won't be easy.

61
00:03:56,627 --> 00:03:58,929
It's clear she doesn't
trust people easily.

62
00:03:59,796 --> 00:04:01,365
She acts exactly like him.

63
00:04:01,999 --> 00:04:03,533
Like father, like daughter.

64
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:07,004
(Atelier)

65
00:04:07,004 --> 00:04:09,840
(Inner Landscapes: The Flow of Emotion
Choi Hee Su Solo Exhibition)

66
00:04:20,951 --> 00:04:22,986
Which piece are you most attached to?

67
00:04:22,986 --> 00:04:26,256
This is my first solo exhibition in Korea,

68
00:04:26,256 --> 00:04:30,093
so I tried to put a bit of my emotions
into each piece.

69
00:04:30,093 --> 00:04:31,595
She majored in painting,

70
00:04:32,396 --> 00:04:34,431
and she's fairly well known
in the industry.

71
00:04:35,465 --> 00:04:37,034
Her skills are top-notch.

72
00:04:38,201 --> 00:04:40,237
She's not some rich girl...

73
00:04:41,305 --> 00:04:43,006
who lives off her family and does nothing.

74
00:04:45,909 --> 00:04:47,945
The only way to meet Choi Young Ho...

75
00:04:48,845 --> 00:04:51,381
is to approach this girl
and wait for an opening.

76
00:04:52,983 --> 00:04:55,218
I don't see any other way.

77
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:05,729
This is where it gets difficult.

78
00:05:06,897 --> 00:05:08,832
Think carefully about how to approach her,

79
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,568
then act with caution.

80
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:14,471
There must be countless people
swarming around,

81
00:05:15,038 --> 00:05:17,074
looking for a way to get something...

82
00:05:17,074 --> 00:05:18,508
out of that rich man.

83
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:22,679
The moment you look like one of them,
your chance is gone.

84
00:05:22,980 --> 00:05:23,847
Forever.

85
00:05:36,727 --> 00:05:38,228
Sorry, but let's finish the interview.

86
00:05:38,228 --> 00:05:39,763
Please take a good look around.

87
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:41,565
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

88
00:06:19,169 --> 00:06:20,203
Hello.

89
00:06:23,807 --> 00:06:25,442
For a moment, I had this thought.

90
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:28,312
Maybe my target...

91
00:06:28,312 --> 00:06:30,714
should include the daughter
Choi Young Ho treasures so much,

92
00:06:32,382 --> 00:06:34,184
Choi Hee Su too.

93
00:06:36,987 --> 00:06:39,723
He killed someone else's family
while protecting his own blood,

94
00:06:39,723 --> 00:06:42,459
so maybe that would be
a more fitting way...

95
00:06:43,126 --> 00:06:45,529
to take revenge on that shameless old man.

96
00:06:45,796 --> 00:06:47,431
Do you like the painting?

97
00:06:49,499 --> 00:06:51,268
That's when one idea came to me.

98
00:06:52,402 --> 00:06:53,704
- Thank you.
- Maybe,

99
00:06:55,272 --> 00:06:56,673
Choi Young Ho's end...

100
00:06:58,275 --> 00:07:00,177
will be crueler than I expected.

101
00:07:02,913 --> 00:07:05,449
Because there's no such thing
as revenge that only gives back...

102
00:07:07,417 --> 00:07:08,452
what was done to you.

103
00:07:11,755 --> 00:07:15,125
(Revenge)

104
00:07:27,971 --> 00:07:29,640
Come here, honey.

105
00:07:31,074 --> 00:07:32,776
I'm home.

106
00:07:33,777 --> 00:07:35,812
Why do you look so down?

107
00:07:36,246 --> 00:07:37,314
Did something happen?

108
00:07:37,614 --> 00:07:39,349
- No, nothing.
- Really?

109
00:07:40,917 --> 00:07:41,985
Ms. Ham Myo Jin.

110
00:07:42,552 --> 00:07:43,620
You have a package.

111
00:07:55,165 --> 00:07:57,501
Here's your package.

112
00:07:59,569 --> 00:08:00,404
Thanks.

113
00:08:15,886 --> 00:08:16,720
What?

114
00:08:20,891 --> 00:08:21,725
No way.

115
00:08:23,627 --> 00:08:24,461
This...

116
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:27,197
Dad.

117
00:08:27,798 --> 00:08:28,999
You'll get hurt, careful.

118
00:08:29,866 --> 00:08:32,469
Dad, I wanted this so badly.

119
00:08:32,469 --> 00:08:33,637
Do you think your dad
or mom wouldn't know...

120
00:08:33,637 --> 00:08:35,939
what you want?

121
00:08:35,939 --> 00:08:38,775
I'm going to draw so well with this.

122
00:08:38,775 --> 00:08:39,843
All right.

123
00:08:39,843 --> 00:08:42,312
- My pretty girl.
- I love it.

124
00:08:58,295 --> 00:09:01,465
(Cheongham Flower Farm)

125
00:09:04,034 --> 00:09:04,868
There.

126
00:09:05,736 --> 00:09:06,570
Mom.

127
00:09:07,938 --> 00:09:09,339
That's pretty.

128
00:09:09,906 --> 00:09:11,008
Three flowers?

129
00:09:11,508 --> 00:09:12,609
Is that our family?

130
00:09:12,609 --> 00:09:13,443
Yes.

131
00:09:15,045 --> 00:09:17,848
Who did you get those crafty hands from?

132
00:09:20,717 --> 00:09:21,551
Myo Jin.

133
00:09:22,185 --> 00:09:24,121
- I'm going fishing.
- What?

134
00:09:24,755 --> 00:09:25,922
Wait for me!

135
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:29,259
Hey, you'll fall.

136
00:09:29,259 --> 00:09:30,494
Be careful.

137
00:09:35,499 --> 00:09:36,733
Goodness.

138
00:10:35,726 --> 00:10:37,728
I never imagined...

139
00:10:39,763 --> 00:10:41,164
this was how you and I would end.

140
00:10:41,164 --> 00:10:42,099
Shut up.

141
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:45,469
Even if you went back a hundred times,

142
00:10:46,436 --> 00:10:49,106
you'd do the same thing.
That's who you are.

143
00:15:01,558 --> 00:15:02,559
Please.

144
00:15:03,327 --> 00:15:04,928
Please!

145
00:15:11,735 --> 00:15:13,470
Even after your memories came back,

146
00:15:14,338 --> 00:15:16,306
even after you learned everything,

147
00:15:18,008 --> 00:15:18,909
please,

148
00:15:19,576 --> 00:15:21,144
if you had just pretended not to know,

149
00:15:24,247 --> 00:15:26,083
we could've been happy.

150
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:27,818
Shut up, you evil bastard.

151
00:15:36,927 --> 00:15:38,495
Over one stupid memory?

152
00:15:39,463 --> 00:15:41,765
It's already over and gone.

153
00:15:43,867 --> 00:15:46,136
You're the one trapped in old memories.

154
00:15:48,538 --> 00:15:50,507
You're the one who can't get out.

155
00:15:53,810 --> 00:15:54,745
I'll kill you.

156
00:15:55,979 --> 00:15:56,780
Yes.

157
00:15:57,948 --> 00:15:58,849
Yes.

158
00:16:01,285 --> 00:16:03,020
I wish that too.

159
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:06,690
I wish...

160
00:16:11,395 --> 00:16:12,296
someone...

161
00:16:13,964 --> 00:16:15,132
would stop me.

162
00:16:22,606 --> 00:16:23,507
Yes.

163
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,210
Let's go together.

164
00:16:32,149 --> 00:16:33,283
Ryu Jun Ho, stop.

165
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:34,151
Now.

166
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:38,722
Let go of her.

167
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:50,667
Damn it.

168
00:17:02,112 --> 00:17:03,246
Ms. Ham.

169
00:17:03,246 --> 00:17:04,581
Ms. Ham, wake up.

170
00:17:12,623 --> 00:17:13,590
Please wake up.

171
00:17:18,762 --> 00:17:20,230
I'm home.

172
00:17:20,230 --> 00:17:22,766
Honey, how was school?

173
00:17:22,766 --> 00:17:25,035
I bought snacks.

174
00:17:25,035 --> 00:17:25,836
Wait.

175
00:17:26,603 --> 00:17:27,604
Dad, what happened to your arm?

176
00:17:27,604 --> 00:17:30,474
This, well...

177
00:17:30,474 --> 00:17:31,541
- Right.
- Yeah?

178
00:17:31,942 --> 00:17:34,378
Did you tell your art club friends
to come over?

179
00:17:34,878 --> 00:17:37,614
I'll buy something tasty,
so bring everyone.

180
00:17:37,614 --> 00:17:40,217
You can all draw on that computer
and have fun.

181
00:17:41,318 --> 00:17:42,786
No, it's embarrassing.

182
00:17:43,754 --> 00:17:44,955
Embarrassing?

183
00:17:46,790 --> 00:17:48,425
I'm the only one without my own room.

184
00:17:48,425 --> 00:17:49,793
I don't want to invite my friends.

185
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:51,962
I see.

186
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:56,466
But Dad, how did you hurt your arm?

187
00:17:57,467 --> 00:17:58,535
This?

188
00:17:59,803 --> 00:18:02,539
Earlier,

189
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:04,508
- I was working in the field and...
- Yeah?

190
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:17,955
When the kids see our place,
they'll think it's kind of shabby, right?

191
00:18:17,955 --> 00:18:21,491
I told you not to keep telling her
to bring friends over.

192
00:18:21,491 --> 00:18:22,893
You're so clueless.

193
00:18:26,163 --> 00:18:27,030
Well,

194
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:31,168
Myo Jin does need...

195
00:18:32,436 --> 00:18:34,304
her own room now.

196
00:18:36,607 --> 00:18:38,342
Of course, she does.

197
00:18:40,210 --> 00:18:43,447
Our daughter is a grown young lady now.

198
00:18:46,783 --> 00:18:47,851
With our situation,

199
00:18:49,786 --> 00:18:53,223
when could we ever find a place
with a proper room?

200
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:58,228
Just wait and see.

201
00:18:58,228 --> 00:18:59,162
This time,

202
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:02,733
who knows if we might get picked
for public housing?

203
00:19:04,868 --> 00:19:06,737
If we didn't get it last year,

204
00:19:07,704 --> 00:19:09,206
why would we get it this year?

205
00:19:11,008 --> 00:19:13,110
You and your bad luck.

206
00:19:14,344 --> 00:19:16,880
We need to give Myo Jin her own room.

207
00:19:20,384 --> 00:19:21,385
Still,

208
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:24,588
Myo Jin is so bright.

209
00:19:27,824 --> 00:19:29,593
That puts my mind at ease.

210
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,128
Goodness.

211
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,931
Do you think she isn't hurting inside?

212
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:37,868
She just doesn't say it.

213
00:19:41,038 --> 00:19:42,606
Do you think I don't know...

214
00:19:45,108 --> 00:19:46,977
how deep-hearted Myo Jin is?

215
00:19:51,648 --> 00:19:54,184
You have to leave for work at dawn.
Go to sleep.

216
00:20:38,729 --> 00:20:40,097
I don't need anything else.

217
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:42,332
Just tell me this.

218
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,836
Did you kill my mom and dad?

219
00:20:48,438 --> 00:20:49,439
Myo Jin!

220
00:20:51,808 --> 00:20:53,243
Do you miss your parents?

221
00:20:54,478 --> 00:20:56,380
Will you only be satisfied
after seeing blood?

222
00:20:56,847 --> 00:20:58,248
If you want revenge,

223
00:20:58,682 --> 00:21:00,684
get your head on straight first.

224
00:21:01,118 --> 00:21:03,086
Do whatever it takes
to recover your memories.

225
00:21:03,754 --> 00:21:05,455
The things I told you.

226
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:07,924
No matter how bad the accident was,

227
00:21:08,525 --> 00:21:09,393
they're not something...

228
00:21:10,093 --> 00:21:12,062
you can just forget.

229
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:13,630
I tried hundreds of times,

230
00:21:14,031 --> 00:21:15,499
but nothing worked.

231
00:21:17,034 --> 00:21:19,436
Coming to you was
the last thing I could do.

232
00:21:19,436 --> 00:21:21,571
It isn't true that I confessed
to the police...

233
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:23,573
I set the fire by mistake.

234
00:21:24,675 --> 00:21:26,910
The truth I hid
even when I went to prison...

235
00:21:27,611 --> 00:21:30,414
and told only you.

236
00:21:31,181 --> 00:21:32,950
You still don't remember it?

237
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:35,252
None of it?

238
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:37,454
Tell me...

239
00:21:38,622 --> 00:21:39,856
what happened.

240
00:21:42,192 --> 00:21:44,528
Who killed my mom and dad, and why?

241
00:21:58,041 --> 00:22:01,111
This cancer is eating my body away.

242
00:22:12,656 --> 00:22:14,558
I don't know what'll happen or when.

243
00:22:15,592 --> 00:22:16,660
So I kept something.

244
00:22:26,903 --> 00:22:28,639
I told you...

245
00:22:30,607 --> 00:22:32,909
the first time you came
saying you'd kill me.

246
00:22:33,543 --> 00:22:34,645
A guy like me...

247
00:22:35,879 --> 00:22:37,347
doesn't trust the world.

248
00:22:39,583 --> 00:22:41,718
What you can trust isn't people or money.

249
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:45,922
It's the insurance you keep on them.

250
00:22:47,190 --> 00:22:48,191
Lee Jong Su.

251
00:22:49,593 --> 00:22:52,029
He's the guy who brought
Chairman Choi Young Ho's money.

252
00:22:53,297 --> 00:22:55,299
I recorded my conversation with him.

253
00:22:55,832 --> 00:22:57,367
There will come a time when you need it.

254
00:22:58,001 --> 00:22:59,069
Then this is...

255
00:23:00,037 --> 00:23:00,971
Listen to it.

256
00:23:01,905 --> 00:23:04,408
You won't have anything left
to wonder about.

257
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:09,780
Now go.

258
00:23:11,381 --> 00:23:12,950
And don't ever come back.

259
00:23:18,488 --> 00:23:19,856
I won't be here even if you do.

260
00:24:08,972 --> 00:24:09,873
Seriously?

261
00:24:10,674 --> 00:24:14,211
They make me do
all kinds of ridiculous crap.

262
00:24:17,180 --> 00:24:18,115
This is it.

263
00:24:30,694 --> 00:24:32,796
Are you on your way back
from the hospital?

264
00:24:34,932 --> 00:24:36,733
I cleaned this morning.

265
00:24:36,733 --> 00:24:38,735
I just did this
while I was cleaning the second floor.

266
00:24:38,735 --> 00:24:40,337
By the way, what did the hospital say?

267
00:24:41,438 --> 00:24:43,640
They said I'm recovering
faster than expected...

268
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:45,542
and told me to take
even better care of myself.

269
00:24:45,542 --> 00:24:47,744
See? What did I tell you?

270
00:24:47,744 --> 00:24:50,047
If you do what I say,
you'll get better in no time.

271
00:24:50,547 --> 00:24:51,448
I'm happy for you.

272
00:25:12,235 --> 00:25:15,105
(Atibam)

273
00:25:47,537 --> 00:25:48,805
Good morning.

274
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,911
Is there any place in particular
that feels uncomfortable?

275
00:25:56,013 --> 00:25:57,347
No, I'm fine.

276
00:25:58,482 --> 00:26:01,285
Your test results are all normal.

277
00:26:01,652 --> 00:26:02,552
That's a relief.

278
00:26:03,020 --> 00:26:05,188
The anesthetic that paralyzed your body...

279
00:26:05,188 --> 00:26:06,990
has been completely cleared.

280
00:26:07,291 --> 00:26:09,326
You're healthy enough...

281
00:26:09,326 --> 00:26:10,294
to be discharged today.

282
00:26:11,161 --> 00:26:12,195
Thank you.

283
00:26:15,198 --> 00:26:16,099
Doctor.

284
00:26:18,001 --> 00:26:20,570
Can I ask what happened to Ryu Jun Ho?

285
00:26:22,873 --> 00:26:25,475
You mean the suspect
with the gunshot wound?

286
00:26:26,643 --> 00:26:27,477
Yes.

287
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:31,114
I heard his injuries are serious,
so he's in the ICU.

288
00:26:33,417 --> 00:26:35,085
If he's in the ICU,

289
00:26:36,153 --> 00:26:38,088
does that mean his life isn't in danger?

290
00:26:38,422 --> 00:26:39,756
Yes, that's right.

291
00:26:40,524 --> 00:26:42,426
Even if someone is a major criminal,

292
00:26:42,426 --> 00:26:43,860
in cases like this,

293
00:26:43,860 --> 00:26:44,962
for the sake of the investigation,

294
00:26:44,962 --> 00:26:46,997
they usually do everything they can
to keep them alive.

295
00:26:48,131 --> 00:26:49,433
Is he in this hospital?

296
00:26:50,334 --> 00:26:51,201
No.

297
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:52,769
Since he's a murder suspect,

298
00:26:52,769 --> 00:26:54,538
he's under separate protection.

299
00:26:55,238 --> 00:26:57,441
He's under special police supervision,

300
00:26:57,441 --> 00:26:59,910
so even we don't know where he is.

301
00:27:00,744 --> 00:27:02,112
I see.

302
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:04,514
Take care.

303
00:27:14,691 --> 00:27:18,895
(Seoul Namyeong Police Station)

304
00:27:19,196 --> 00:27:20,564
It seems Ryu Jun Ho...

305
00:27:20,564 --> 00:27:23,600
planned to make it look as though you,

306
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:25,869
after killing Choi Young Ho
and Choi Hee Su to avenge your parents,

307
00:27:26,770 --> 00:27:29,439
also killed Wang Gi Cheol,

308
00:27:29,439 --> 00:27:31,208
who was paid to give
false testimony for them,

309
00:27:31,208 --> 00:27:34,177
and then staged everything
as an impulsive suicide...

310
00:27:34,177 --> 00:27:36,747
caused by traumatic brain injury.

311
00:27:37,447 --> 00:27:40,550
Even though he knew you were recovering,

312
00:27:41,051 --> 00:27:43,387
he kept making you take
medication for schizophrenia,

313
00:27:43,754 --> 00:27:45,822
deleted the recordings...

314
00:27:45,822 --> 00:27:48,158
that could have exposed his past actions,

315
00:27:48,558 --> 00:27:49,927
and they were all part
of the same pattern.

316
00:27:53,063 --> 00:27:54,498
On the day of the incident,

317
00:27:55,065 --> 00:27:56,566
the secretary, Director Kim Won Il,

318
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,770
used a forged passport
and attended the conference in Germany...

319
00:27:59,770 --> 00:28:01,838
in Ryu Jun Ho's place.

320
00:28:02,239 --> 00:28:04,441
But when we actually began
tracing his accounts,

321
00:28:04,908 --> 00:28:06,276
he confessed to everything.

322
00:28:09,246 --> 00:28:10,714
How are you feeling, Ms. Ham?

323
00:28:13,850 --> 00:28:16,153
Thanks to you, I'm much better, Detective.

324
00:28:16,153 --> 00:28:17,654
I don't have to go
to the hospital anymore, either.

325
00:28:18,689 --> 00:28:19,856
That's really good to hear.

326
00:28:20,457 --> 00:28:23,026
What happens from here?

327
00:28:24,261 --> 00:28:25,395
In about two weeks,

328
00:28:25,395 --> 00:28:27,898
the full investigation will begin.

329
00:28:27,898 --> 00:28:30,400
In the end,
it'll become a battle over sentencing.

330
00:28:32,135 --> 00:28:33,036
I see.

331
00:28:33,637 --> 00:28:36,239
Ryu Jun Ho is currently
exercising his right to remain silent,

332
00:28:36,239 --> 00:28:38,809
so we still haven't heard directly...

333
00:28:38,809 --> 00:28:40,811
why he tried to kill you, Ms. Ham.

334
00:28:42,079 --> 00:28:42,980
Detective.

335
00:28:44,247 --> 00:28:46,249
If Ryu Jun Ho is staying silent...

336
00:28:47,884 --> 00:28:49,486
What you're assuming is right.

337
00:28:49,987 --> 00:28:51,622
The country's top law firm
is representing him.

338
00:28:52,623 --> 00:28:54,424
He's rich,

339
00:28:54,424 --> 00:28:56,627
so he's put together
an extremely high-end defense team.

340
00:28:59,630 --> 00:29:00,731
Now,

341
00:29:00,731 --> 00:29:03,533
has your suspicion about Ms. Ham's
Jebu-do Island accident...

342
00:29:03,533 --> 00:29:05,068
been cleared up, Detective Woo?

343
00:29:05,068 --> 00:29:06,536
Of course.

344
00:29:07,170 --> 00:29:08,739
I've been very rude all this time.

345
00:29:11,742 --> 00:29:14,111
She went all the way to the villa
to save Choi Hee Su...

346
00:29:14,878 --> 00:29:16,413
and nearly lost her life.

347
00:29:17,014 --> 00:29:19,116
The shock of that moment
and the accident...

348
00:29:19,750 --> 00:29:21,952
are what have tormented Ms. Ham until now.

349
00:29:22,185 --> 00:29:23,654
I'm glad the misunderstanding
has been cleared up.

350
00:29:25,389 --> 00:29:26,790
I have a favor to ask.

351
00:29:28,892 --> 00:29:31,128
Please let me see Ryu Jun Ho
one last time.

352
00:29:39,202 --> 00:29:40,837
I want to return it to him myself.

353
00:29:43,674 --> 00:29:45,375
Yes, of course.

354
00:29:46,243 --> 00:29:47,244
Thank you.

355
00:29:59,656 --> 00:30:00,757
Questioning as a witness?

356
00:30:00,757 --> 00:30:01,825
What bullshit.

357
00:30:02,526 --> 00:30:03,860
I wasn't born yesterday.

358
00:30:04,494 --> 00:30:06,897
It's all because of that idiot.

359
00:30:07,531 --> 00:30:09,633
I'll never work with
brainless bastards again.

360
00:30:10,167 --> 00:30:11,101
Damn it.

361
00:30:17,908 --> 00:30:19,409
I'm sorry! Are you hurt?

362
00:30:21,478 --> 00:30:22,346
No.

363
00:30:23,313 --> 00:30:24,314
Are you Korean?

364
00:30:24,915 --> 00:30:26,617
Do you speak Korean?

365
00:30:27,084 --> 00:30:29,052
Well, I'm an overseas Chinese.

366
00:30:29,453 --> 00:30:30,554
But are you okay?

367
00:30:30,554 --> 00:30:31,421
Are you hurt?

368
00:30:31,421 --> 00:30:32,289
I'm sorry.

369
00:30:32,656 --> 00:30:33,757
I'm okay.

370
00:30:35,258 --> 00:30:36,793
I missed my flight last week,

371
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:38,829
so I was rushing a little today
and caused this accident.

372
00:30:41,698 --> 00:30:43,834
I wish there were
more flights to Hong Kong.

373
00:30:44,101 --> 00:30:45,035
Are you going to Hong Kong?

374
00:30:45,869 --> 00:30:47,204
Same as me.

375
00:30:47,204 --> 00:30:48,605
- Really?
- Yes.

376
00:30:49,006 --> 00:30:51,375
I go every week for work.

377
00:30:53,510 --> 00:30:54,611
But the time...

378
00:30:57,047 --> 00:30:58,849
Would you like to talk
while we go together?

379
00:30:59,182 --> 00:31:00,117
Sure.

380
00:31:01,318 --> 00:31:02,252
Let's go.

381
00:31:02,252 --> 00:31:03,120
Thanks.

382
00:31:36,086 --> 00:31:37,921
(Restricted Area)

383
00:31:44,761 --> 00:31:46,797
I did receive Detective Woo's call,

384
00:31:47,431 --> 00:31:48,498
but because of the patient's condition,

385
00:31:49,066 --> 00:31:50,567
I can't give you much time.

386
00:31:51,802 --> 00:31:52,903
Yes, I understand.

387
00:31:53,804 --> 00:31:55,372
When you're finished,

388
00:31:55,372 --> 00:31:56,607
press this button.

389
00:31:57,941 --> 00:31:59,876
Then a nurse will come and escort you out.

390
00:32:01,578 --> 00:32:04,281
Can he hear my voice?

391
00:32:05,148 --> 00:32:05,916
Yes.

392
00:32:07,117 --> 00:32:07,951
Mr. Ryu.

393
00:32:08,585 --> 00:32:09,920
Ms. Ham is here.

394
00:32:55,399 --> 00:32:56,867
I was afraid.

395
00:33:03,774 --> 00:33:06,276
If your memories came back,

396
00:33:08,478 --> 00:33:10,247
you'd learn everything,

397
00:33:14,251 --> 00:33:16,620
and you'd leave me.

398
00:33:21,391 --> 00:33:22,693
Then I'd go back...

399
00:33:24,828 --> 00:33:26,763
to the past again.

400
00:33:43,213 --> 00:33:44,481
For one brief moment,

401
00:33:48,719 --> 00:33:49,720
there was a time...

402
00:33:51,355 --> 00:33:53,523
when I doubted you.

403
00:34:09,539 --> 00:34:10,941
(Voice Mail)

404
00:34:10,941 --> 00:34:12,442
(You have a new voice message.)

405
00:34:14,478 --> 00:34:15,412
Jun Ho.

406
00:34:15,912 --> 00:34:18,181
Your phone is off,
so I'll leave a voice message.

407
00:34:19,416 --> 00:34:20,484
Tonight,

408
00:34:21,318 --> 00:34:22,986
I don't think I can meet you.

409
00:34:29,693 --> 00:34:31,495
I should have stopped then.

410
00:34:37,134 --> 00:34:38,936
It was the last chance...

411
00:34:42,039 --> 00:34:43,307
to get away from you,

412
00:34:46,977 --> 00:34:48,412
but I threw it away.

413
00:34:51,615 --> 00:34:52,482
That's right.

414
00:34:58,422 --> 00:35:00,290
Every choice was yours.

415
00:35:05,495 --> 00:35:08,231
You must have hoped
my memories would never return.

416
00:35:10,334 --> 00:35:11,602
Because you wanted me
to forget everything...

417
00:35:13,103 --> 00:35:15,973
and live inside the cage you built for us.

418
00:35:16,873 --> 00:35:19,509
(Change of Address Form, Ham Myo Jin)

419
00:35:22,913 --> 00:35:24,314
Here you go.

420
00:35:24,615 --> 00:35:25,983
Yes, that's all set.

421
00:35:30,687 --> 00:35:31,655
This is him.

422
00:35:33,290 --> 00:35:34,091
Okay.

423
00:35:50,741 --> 00:35:51,575
What?

424
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:59,049
But my feelings remembered you,

425
00:36:00,851 --> 00:36:02,886
and they showed me what I had to do.

426
00:36:08,292 --> 00:36:10,060
I came to say thank you.

427
00:36:11,895 --> 00:36:13,997
After the accident,
if it hadn't been for you,

428
00:36:16,099 --> 00:36:18,168
none of this would have been possible.

429
00:36:30,981 --> 00:36:32,316
The police said...

430
00:36:35,619 --> 00:36:37,621
I killed...

431
00:36:41,558 --> 00:36:42,492
Hee Su.

432
00:36:43,126 --> 00:36:45,429
What do they mean, I killed her?

433
00:36:46,964 --> 00:36:47,798
That day,

434
00:36:53,003 --> 00:36:56,807
I did try to kill those two,

435
00:36:59,076 --> 00:37:00,143
but I didn't...

436
00:37:03,847 --> 00:37:04,748
think of...

437
00:37:05,515 --> 00:37:06,516
doing so brutally.

438
00:37:08,285 --> 00:37:09,453
At least,

439
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:14,291
I never...

440
00:37:17,461 --> 00:37:19,229
thought of doing it that way.

441
00:37:32,175 --> 00:37:33,043
Was it...

442
00:37:38,215 --> 00:37:39,516
you?

443
00:37:41,285 --> 00:37:42,419
Don't be curious.

444
00:37:44,354 --> 00:37:46,623
It's meaningless to you now anyway.

445
00:37:47,391 --> 00:37:48,358
Were...

446
00:37:52,296 --> 00:37:54,498
all the moments you spent with me...

447
00:37:56,266 --> 00:37:57,100
really...

448
00:38:01,405 --> 00:38:04,141
all lies?

449
00:38:06,176 --> 00:38:08,145
I'm surprised...

450
00:38:09,046 --> 00:38:10,080
you still wonder that.

451
00:38:17,955 --> 00:38:19,022
Why...

452
00:38:22,759 --> 00:38:24,728
be that cruel?

453
00:38:26,330 --> 00:38:27,197
Because that day,

454
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,536
you were the one who set fire to my house.

455
00:38:34,805 --> 00:38:35,739
Because you...

456
00:38:36,607 --> 00:38:39,076
are the murderer
who killed my mom and dad.

457
00:38:56,393 --> 00:38:58,195
You'd better brace yourself.

458
00:39:07,137 --> 00:39:09,573
Until your whole body rots away,

459
00:39:10,907 --> 00:39:12,175
slowly, step by step,

460
00:39:13,644 --> 00:39:15,145
I'm going to break you down.

461
00:39:18,015 --> 00:39:19,049
Please...

462
00:39:22,085 --> 00:39:23,153
die slowly.

463
00:39:45,309 --> 00:39:47,577
(No Unauthorized Entry)

464
00:41:29,179 --> 00:41:30,747
(The late Ham Jun Seong, Lee Yoo Jeong,
2010.03.16)

465
00:41:30,747 --> 00:41:31,915
(Mom, Dad, rest in peace.)

466
00:41:32,349 --> 00:41:33,350
Dad.

467
00:41:35,819 --> 00:41:36,720
Mom.

468
00:41:39,323 --> 00:41:40,357
I'm here.

469
00:41:42,392 --> 00:41:43,660
I'm sorry...

470
00:41:46,997 --> 00:41:47,931
I came so late.

471
00:42:11,154 --> 00:42:12,189
Welcome.

472
00:42:14,791 --> 00:42:15,959
It's been a while.

473
00:42:21,598 --> 00:42:23,700
One pour-over coffee, please.

474
00:42:25,702 --> 00:42:26,870
It's all right.

475
00:42:27,371 --> 00:42:29,973
I'm curious to taste the coffee
you make yourself, Ms. Ham.

476
00:43:11,982 --> 00:43:12,950
It's good.

477
00:43:14,985 --> 00:43:16,420
It feels perfect.

478
00:43:24,161 --> 00:43:25,195
Last week,

479
00:43:25,829 --> 00:43:27,998
the police came
as part of the investigation.

480
00:43:28,865 --> 00:43:30,867
I heard about your parents, Ms. Ham,

481
00:43:31,535 --> 00:43:33,537
and looked up the articles
from back then too.

482
00:43:34,605 --> 00:43:37,975
The reactions you showed
during the initial tests...

483
00:43:38,442 --> 00:43:41,011
seemed like unrelated answers every time,

484
00:43:41,712 --> 00:43:44,281
but when I analyzed them again,
that wasn't the case.

485
00:43:50,988 --> 00:43:52,889
A thought suddenly occurred to me.

486
00:43:54,257 --> 00:43:55,892
Maybe everyone, myself included,

487
00:43:55,892 --> 00:43:58,061
was completely fooled.

488
00:43:58,595 --> 00:44:00,530
Choi Hee Su, Ryu Jun Ho,

489
00:44:00,530 --> 00:44:02,866
Chairman Choi Young Ho and Wang Gi Cheol.

490
00:44:03,467 --> 00:44:06,970
Everyone who brought tragedy
to your family is dead,

491
00:44:07,971 --> 00:44:09,306
and that can't be a coincidence.

492
00:44:14,077 --> 00:44:16,213
Is that how I look to you, Doctor?

493
00:44:16,913 --> 00:44:18,782
I didn't come here with any other reason.

494
00:44:19,449 --> 00:44:20,651
As a doctor,

495
00:44:20,651 --> 00:44:22,786
I was left with one unanswered question.

496
00:44:25,689 --> 00:44:26,957
When did it start?

497
00:44:27,924 --> 00:44:30,227
When did you begin hiding
that your memories had returned?

498
00:44:31,561 --> 00:44:33,330
Even if I told you,

499
00:44:34,097 --> 00:44:35,532
it wouldn't matter anymore.

500
00:44:36,767 --> 00:44:37,634
Why not?

501
00:44:40,203 --> 00:44:41,471
Because memories...

502
00:44:42,306 --> 00:44:43,540
belong to the past,

503
00:44:47,077 --> 00:44:49,046
and the past can't be undone.

504
00:44:51,281 --> 00:44:52,449
I told you.

505
00:44:52,683 --> 00:44:55,352
Back then, we got acceptance letters
from the best universities in America.

506
00:44:55,352 --> 00:44:56,219
Can that...

507
00:44:58,121 --> 00:45:00,290
be a reason to kill people?

508
00:45:05,262 --> 00:45:07,164
People with nothing to lose...

509
00:45:08,031 --> 00:45:10,534
all think like you, of course.

510
00:45:11,935 --> 00:45:12,769
What?

511
00:45:14,871 --> 00:45:15,706
You.

512
00:45:16,239 --> 00:45:18,475
When you first came to my exhibition
and saw my paintings, you cried.

513
00:45:19,409 --> 00:45:20,477
You said it yourself...

514
00:45:21,345 --> 00:45:23,146
that you could feel
my sorrow inside my paintings.

515
00:45:23,513 --> 00:45:24,448
My passion,

516
00:45:25,082 --> 00:45:27,284
my talent, all of it, so vividly.

517
00:45:27,918 --> 00:45:29,853
You said that you'd never felt
anything like it before.

518
00:45:31,355 --> 00:45:32,522
You're insane.

519
00:45:33,890 --> 00:45:36,226
If those people had ruined me back then,

520
00:45:42,532 --> 00:45:43,600
my paintings...

521
00:45:45,869 --> 00:45:47,437
wouldn't exist in the world now.

522
00:45:51,508 --> 00:45:52,876
Can you even imagine that?

523
00:46:03,553 --> 00:46:04,454
Hey.

524
00:46:04,721 --> 00:46:07,424
Do you know
what people with nothing to lose...

525
00:46:08,992 --> 00:46:10,794
are capable of?

526
00:46:14,965 --> 00:46:16,099
They just wait for their chance.

527
00:46:16,967 --> 00:46:19,569
They wait to find fault
with people who have money,

528
00:46:19,937 --> 00:46:21,838
and when they get the chance,
they pounce and rip them apart.

529
00:46:21,838 --> 00:46:22,673
Like animals.

530
00:46:23,674 --> 00:46:25,475
That's what happened to us that day.

531
00:46:26,376 --> 00:46:28,512
There is no one in this world
who has nothing to lose.

532
00:46:29,446 --> 00:46:31,848
Because those people were
someone's father and someone's mother too.

533
00:46:31,848 --> 00:46:33,617
Stop with the pathetic sob story.

534
00:46:35,485 --> 00:46:37,454
Who do you think you are
to talk to me like that?

535
00:46:37,454 --> 00:46:38,855
Are you saying I should've been ruined...

536
00:46:38,855 --> 00:46:40,991
because of people like them?

537
00:46:41,425 --> 00:46:42,225
I...

538
00:46:42,626 --> 00:46:44,428
am not like those people.

539
00:46:45,128 --> 00:46:47,564
I'm not one of those beastly types
who swarm like dogs...

540
00:46:47,564 --> 00:46:49,800
at the slightest opening
just to squeeze money out of people.

541
00:47:39,616 --> 00:47:40,450
This is insane.

542
00:47:41,652 --> 00:47:42,719
They're all insane.

543
00:48:09,313 --> 00:48:11,348
Why is it so noisy?

544
00:48:33,303 --> 00:48:34,137
Hee Su.

545
00:48:34,471 --> 00:48:35,372
Hee Su.

546
00:49:36,066 --> 00:49:38,068
Suspected traffic accident patient.

547
00:49:38,068 --> 00:49:40,237
Blood pressure 90 over 60.

548
00:49:40,537 --> 00:49:41,872
Ryu Jun Ho...

549
00:49:41,872 --> 00:49:43,607
Suspected thoracoabdominal trauma
and femur fracture.

550
00:49:43,607 --> 00:49:46,576
- killed...
- Requesting trauma team standby.

551
00:49:46,977 --> 00:49:49,947
- my mom and dad.
- Copy. The trauma team will stand by.

552
00:49:49,947 --> 00:49:51,048
I mustn't...

553
00:49:52,015 --> 00:49:53,617
- forget.
- Patient is being transported.

554
00:49:53,617 --> 00:49:55,118
The patient is unresponsive.

555
00:49:55,118 --> 00:49:56,453
That man...

556
00:49:58,722 --> 00:49:59,723
killed...

557
00:50:00,824 --> 00:50:02,192
my mom and...

558
00:50:02,192 --> 00:50:03,560
Check the bleeding sites again.

559
00:50:04,695 --> 00:50:07,064
(Rescue Team)

560
00:50:12,603 --> 00:50:13,437
Emergency patient.

561
00:50:13,437 --> 00:50:15,172
She was conscious at the scene,

562
00:50:15,172 --> 00:50:16,907
but lost consciousness again
during transport.

563
00:50:16,907 --> 00:50:18,375
Move her to the OR quickly.

564
00:50:18,375 --> 00:50:19,943
- Call a surgeon.
- Yes.

565
00:50:19,943 --> 00:50:21,078
(Central Surgery Center)

566
00:50:29,019 --> 00:50:29,886
Ma'am.

567
00:50:30,120 --> 00:50:31,221
Can you hear me?

568
00:50:31,521 --> 00:50:32,689
Can you hear me?

569
00:50:40,597 --> 00:50:41,365
Yes?

570
00:50:43,267 --> 00:50:44,201
What did you say?

571
00:50:45,102 --> 00:50:46,103
When I wake up,

572
00:50:46,903 --> 00:50:48,171
tell me...

573
00:50:52,376 --> 00:50:53,477
that Ryu Jun Ho...

574
00:50:55,479 --> 00:50:57,147
killed...

575
00:50:58,715 --> 00:50:59,816
my mom and dad.

576
00:51:03,020 --> 00:51:05,622
I must never forget.

577
00:51:10,494 --> 00:51:11,328
I must...

578
00:51:12,963 --> 00:51:14,831
remember.

579
00:51:17,067 --> 00:51:17,935
Ryu...

580
00:51:18,402 --> 00:51:19,369
Jun...

581
00:51:20,570 --> 00:51:21,505
Ho...

582
00:51:42,392 --> 00:51:43,327
Myo Jin.

583
00:51:43,660 --> 00:51:44,928
Please wake up.

584
00:51:48,532 --> 00:51:49,566
Are you coming around?

585
00:51:52,202 --> 00:51:54,071
Jun Ho.

586
00:51:55,439 --> 00:51:56,273
What?

587
00:51:57,407 --> 00:51:58,442
Ryu...

588
00:52:00,777 --> 00:52:02,079
Jun Ho.

589
00:52:02,813 --> 00:52:03,780
Yes, that's right.

590
00:52:05,582 --> 00:52:06,483
It's me.

591
00:52:07,284 --> 00:52:08,585
Ryu Jun Ho.

592
00:52:16,927 --> 00:52:17,861
Myo Jin.

593
00:52:32,676 --> 00:52:33,577
I...

594
00:52:35,245 --> 00:52:36,280
told you, didn't I?

595
00:52:38,515 --> 00:52:39,549
When you...

596
00:52:41,084 --> 00:52:43,053
first woke up after the accident,

597
00:52:46,890 --> 00:52:48,125
you didn't remember your own name,

598
00:52:50,360 --> 00:52:51,495
your family's names,

599
00:52:55,165 --> 00:52:56,300
or anything at all.

600
00:52:57,267 --> 00:52:59,002
Nothing at all.

601
00:53:01,371 --> 00:53:03,206
But...

602
00:53:05,509 --> 00:53:06,777
you only remembered...

603
00:53:09,012 --> 00:53:10,347
my name.

604
00:53:44,815 --> 00:53:46,550
You can forget everything else.

605
00:53:48,986 --> 00:53:49,886
Just keep...

606
00:53:51,355 --> 00:53:52,389
remembering...

607
00:53:56,693 --> 00:53:57,594
only me,

608
00:53:58,829 --> 00:54:00,264
like you do now.

609
00:54:06,169 --> 00:54:07,137
Forever.

610
00:54:25,856 --> 00:54:27,758
Have you ever felt truly terrified?

611
00:54:30,861 --> 00:54:33,397
That fear that everything
could collapse in an instant,

612
00:54:36,433 --> 00:54:40,070
and someone might make
your life turn out that way.

613
00:54:42,239 --> 00:54:45,409
You have a capable father
and someone you love.

614
00:54:46,910 --> 00:54:48,011
What are you afraid of?

615
00:54:52,516 --> 00:54:56,353
Everyone has at least one secret
they can't tell anyone.

616
00:54:59,222 --> 00:55:00,057
Mine...

617
00:55:01,091 --> 00:55:03,627
came too early.

618
00:55:05,529 --> 00:55:06,396
A secret?

619
00:55:07,230 --> 00:55:08,065
Yes.

620
00:55:08,632 --> 00:55:09,499
A secret...

621
00:55:12,336 --> 00:55:15,138
preserved like a specimen
until the day I die,

622
00:55:16,239 --> 00:55:17,608
following me everywhere.

623
00:55:22,212 --> 00:55:23,914
What kind of secret stays hidden forever?

624
00:55:30,787 --> 00:55:31,688
Is that so?

625
00:55:35,459 --> 00:55:38,595
Someone might already know it.

626
00:55:44,368 --> 00:55:45,502
You have...

627
00:55:47,271 --> 00:55:48,138
a secret too.

628
00:55:49,339 --> 00:55:50,173
What?

629
00:55:53,810 --> 00:55:54,678
I,

630
00:55:57,047 --> 00:55:58,115
sometimes,

631
00:55:59,716 --> 00:56:02,152
want to let everything go.

632
00:56:05,856 --> 00:56:07,391
I'm so tired.

633
00:56:12,396 --> 00:56:13,530
It's too hard.

634
00:56:19,403 --> 00:56:20,304
Myo Jin.

635
00:56:22,139 --> 00:56:24,007
Have you ever received a present?

636
00:56:46,229 --> 00:56:47,064
Myo Jin.

637
00:56:47,764 --> 00:56:49,800
Please put that away for me.

638
00:56:51,401 --> 00:56:52,803
That's...

639
00:56:52,803 --> 00:56:55,572
because the chairman and Ms. Choi
have this condition.

640
00:56:56,239 --> 00:56:58,375
They can't look at anything sharp.

641
00:57:02,079 --> 00:57:02,980
A present?

642
00:57:03,747 --> 00:57:05,115
Yes, a present.

643
00:57:08,852 --> 00:57:09,720
I don't know.

644
00:57:10,721 --> 00:57:13,457
I've never lived thinking
about things like that.

645
00:57:20,831 --> 00:57:21,999
Then should I give...

646
00:57:23,200 --> 00:57:24,101
that present to you?

647
00:57:24,835 --> 00:57:25,836
You? To me?

648
00:57:26,703 --> 00:57:27,537
Why?

649
00:57:29,139 --> 00:57:30,007
Just...

650
00:57:34,678 --> 00:57:36,713
because when I look at you sometimes,

651
00:57:39,683 --> 00:57:41,585
you feel similar to me.

652
00:57:53,397 --> 00:57:55,532
There is no one in this world
who has nothing to lose.

653
00:57:56,500 --> 00:57:58,869
Because those people were
someone's father and someone's mother too.

654
00:57:58,869 --> 00:58:00,637
Stop with the pathetic sob story.

655
00:58:02,539 --> 00:58:04,574
Who do you think you are
to talk to me like that?

656
00:58:04,574 --> 00:58:05,809
Are you saying I should've been ruined...

657
00:58:05,809 --> 00:58:08,045
because of people like them?

658
00:58:08,445 --> 00:58:09,246
I...

659
00:58:09,613 --> 00:58:11,381
am not like those people.

660
00:58:12,182 --> 00:58:14,584
I'm not one of those beastly types
who swarm like dogs...

661
00:58:14,584 --> 00:58:16,820
at the slightest opening
just to squeeze money out of people.

662
00:59:45,108 --> 00:59:47,110
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

663
00:59:48,045 --> 00:59:52,783
(REVERSE)
